courses.title: Python
courses.description: Learn about Python fundamentals, best practices, and applications.

cards.question: What is a lambda function in Python?
cards.answer: A lambda function is an anonymous function.

cards.question: What is PEP 8?
cards.answer: PEP 8 is the style guide for writing Python code.

cards.question: What is list comprehension?
cards.answer: A concise way to create lists using a single line of code.

courses.title: Java
courses.description: Learn about Java fundamentals, best practices, and applications.

cards.question: What is JVM?
cards.answer: JVM stands for Java Virtual Machine.

cards.question: What is inheritance in Java?
cards.answer: Inheritance allows a class to inherit features from another class.

cards.question: What is a constructor?
cards.answer: A special method used to initialize objects.

courses.title: C++
courses.description: Learn about C++ fundamentals, best practices, and applications.

cards.question: What is a pointer?
cards.answer: A variable that stores the memory address of another variable.

cards.question: What is the STL?
cards.answer: Standard Template Library provides generic classes and functions.

cards.question: What is a virtual function?
cards.answer: A member function that can be overridden in derived class.

courses.title: Docker
courses.description: Containerize your applications for consistent development and deployment.

cards.question: What is Docker?
cards.answer: Docker is a platform for developing, shipping, and running applications in containers.

cards.question: What is a Dockerfile?
cards.answer: A Dockerfile is a script containing instructions to build a Docker image.

cards.question: What is Docker Hub?
cards.answer: Docker Hub is a cloud-based registry to link code repositories and build Docker images.

courses.title: Linux
courses.description: Master Linux basics, shell scripting, and system administration.

cards.question: What is the root user?
cards.answer: The root user has administrative privileges in a Linux system.

cards.question: What is chmod used for?
cards.answer: chmod changes the file access permissions.

cards.question: What does the ls command do?
cards.answer: ls lists the contents of a directory.

courses.title: JavaScript
courses.description: Learn JavaScript fundamentals and DOM manipulation for dynamic web applications.

cards.question: What is a closure in JavaScript?
cards.answer: A closure is a function having access to the parent scope, even after the parent function has closed.

cards.question: What does 'this' refer to in JavaScript?
cards.answer: 'this' refers to the object that is executing the current function.

cards.question: What is event delegation?
cards.answer: Event delegation is a technique involving adding a single event listener to a parent element.

courses.title: HTML & CSS
courses.description: Build beautiful web pages using semantic HTML and modern CSS.

cards.question: What is the purpose of the alt attribute in images?
cards.answer: It provides alternative text for an image if it cannot be displayed.

cards.question: What is the difference between id and class in CSS?
cards.answer: id is unique per page, while class can be used multiple times.

cards.question: What is flexbox in CSS?
cards.answer: A CSS layout module that makes it easier to design flexible responsive layout structure.

courses.title: React
courses.description: Learn to build fast, interactive user interfaces with React.

cards.question: What is JSX?
cards.answer: JSX is a syntax extension for JavaScript that looks similar to XML or HTML.

cards.question: What are hooks in React?
cards.answer: Hooks are functions that let you use state and other React features without writing a class.

cards.question: What is useEffect used for?
cards.answer: useEffect is used to perform side effects in function components.

courses.title: SQL
courses.description: Learn to manage and query relational databases with SQL.

cards.question: What does SQL stand for?
cards.answer: Structured Query Language.

cards.question: What is a primary key?
cards.answer: A unique identifier for each record in a table.

cards.question: What is the purpose of the JOIN clause?
cards.answer: It combines rows from two or more tables based on a related column.

courses.title: MongoDB
courses.description: Learn to work with NoSQL databases using MongoDB.

cards.question: What type of database is MongoDB?
cards.answer: MongoDB is a NoSQL document database.

cards.question: What is a collection in MongoDB?
cards.answer: A collection is a group of MongoDB documents.

cards.question: How is data stored in MongoDB?
cards.answer: Data is stored in BSON format, a binary representation of JSON.

courses.title: Angular
courses.description: Build scalable web applications using Angular framework.

cards.question: What is Angular?
cards.answer: A TypeScript-based front-end web application framework.

cards.question: What is a component in Angular?
cards.answer: A component controls a patch of screen called a view.

cards.question: What is data binding in Angular?
cards.answer: Data binding is the connection between the component and the DOM.

courses.title: Firebase
courses.description: Use Firebase to build and scale apps with real-time databases and authentication.

cards.question: What is Firebase?
cards.answer: A platform by Google for building web and mobile applications.

cards.question: What is Firestore?
cards.answer: A flexible, scalable NoSQL cloud database to store and sync data.

cards.question: How does Firebase Authentication work?
cards.answer: It provides backend services to authenticate users using only client-side code.

courses.title: Next.js
courses.description: Learn to build optimized and scalable React apps with server-side rendering using Next.js.

cards.question: What is server-side rendering (SSR)?
cards.answer: SSR is rendering a web page on the server instead of the browser.

cards.question: What file defines routes in Next.js?
cards.answer: The 'pages' directory defines routing in Next.js.

cards.question: What is getStaticProps?
cards.answer: getStaticProps allows you to fetch data at build time for static generation.

courses.title: Redis
courses.description: Understand how Redis is used for caching, session management, and real-time analytics.

cards.question: What is Redis?
cards.answer: Redis is an in-memory key-value data store used for caching and fast data retrieval.

cards.question: What data structures does Redis support?
cards.answer: Strings, Lists, Sets, Hashes, Sorted Sets, Bitmaps, and HyperLogLogs.

cards.question: What is the use of TTL in Redis?
cards.answer: TTL defines the time to live for a key before it expires.

bookmarks.question: What is a lambda function in Python?
bookmarks.answer: A lambda function is an anonymous function.

cards.question: What is HTML?
cards.answer: HyperText Markup Language
